data.name: label4.Text
data.value: This repair utility will seek to fix issues with the Stardew Valley Mod Manager. You may be required to reset your application to factory settings. This will not delete any installed mods or Stardew Saves.

data.name: label2.Text
data.value: We're sorry you're having troubles with your software. RWE Labs tests software thoroughly before it is released, but bugs do happen to slip through. If you haven't already, please consider lodging your issue as a bug report if you think this could be a widespread issue.

data.name: label5.Text
data.value:
We'll attempt to fix Stardew Valley Mod Manager without requiring a full reset of the application. This process will include:
- Validating all required directories used by the mod manager. - Resetting application cache data. - Disabling telemetry, checking for SMAPI updates on startup. - Disabling checking updates on startup.

data.name: label10.Text
data.value:
We did our basic repairs but found that there are multiple issues that require a full application reset. This could be because you moved your Stardew Valley Directory (e.g. moving the game to a different hard drive) or had a corrupted file system. Next time you open Stardew Valley Mod Manager, you will be required to complete the setup again. You will lose your existing settings and preferences.
We're sorry for the inconvenience and hope you get set up and running quickly.

data.name: label8.Text
data.value:
We were able to find an issue or two and we attempted to complete some repairs. Please click the button below to launch the application to see if the repairs worked.
If the repairs did not work, please use the "Continue Repairs" button below. Otherwise, click "Finish Repairs" and continue using Stardew Valley Mod Manager as normal.
